  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_4' aria-label=\" South Delhi Municipal Corporation Through its Commissioner versus Bharat Bhushan Jain (Dead) Thr. Lrs. pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('4','2025','2025_12_248_257','2025INSC1324'); ><font size='4'> <strong>SOUTH DELHI MUNICIPAL CORPORATION THROUGH ITS COMMISSIONER<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>BHARAT BHUSHAN JAIN (DEAD) THR. LRS. </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 12 S.C.R. 248</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 1324</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010006652025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : J.B. PARDIWALA<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, K.V. VISWANATHAN<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup></strong><br> Issue for Consideration Issue arose whether the High Court was justified in dismissing the appeal filed by the appellant-South Delhi Municipal Corporation through its Commissioner, thereby affirming the order passed by the District Judge granting plans put forward by the respondents for construction of a residential house. Headnotes&dagger; Delhi Municipal Corporation Act, 1957 &ndash; Deemed sanction of plan for construction of a residential house &ndash; Grant of &ndash; Respondent decided to dismantle 85 years old house which was in a<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 06-11-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CIVIL APPEAL No. 6077/2018</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Disposed off</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-seco